  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I stop Outlook from synchronising folders automatically?",
  "response": "To stop Outlook from synchronizing folders automatically, you can modify the synchronization settings for your account. The exact steps depend on the version of Outlook you're using (Outlook desktop app, Outlook on the web, or mobile app). Below are instructions for the desktop version:\n\n---\n\n### **Stop Automatic Folder Synchronization in Outlook Desktop App**\n1. **Open Outlook**:\n   - Launch the Outlook application on your computer.\n\n2. **Go to Account Settings**:\n   - Click on **File** in the top-left corner.\n   - Select **Account Settings** > **Account Settings** again from the dropdown menu.\n\n3. **Select Your Account**:\n   - In the **Account Settings** window, select the email account you want to modify and click **Change**.\n\n4. **Adjust Synchronization Settings**:\n   - Look for the **More Settings** button and click it.\n   - Go to the **Advanced** tab.\n\n5. **Disable Cached Exchange Mode** (if applicable):\n   - If you're using an Exchange or Office 365 account, uncheck the box for **Use Cached Exchange Mode**. This will stop Outlook from downloading all folders and items automatically.\n\n6. **Limit Synchronized Folders**:\n   - Still in the **Advanced** tab, click the **Offline Folder File Settings** button (if available).\n   - Here, you can choose which folders to synchronize manually and deselect the ones you don\u2019t want to sync automatically.\n\n7. **Save Changes**:\n   - Click **OK**, then **Next**, and **Finish** to apply the changes.\n\n8. **Restart Outlook**:\n   - Close and reopen Outlook for the changes to take effect.\n\n---\n\n### **Stop Automatic Folder Synchronization in Outlook on the Web**\nIf you're using **Outlook on the web (OWA)**:\n- Automatic folder synchronization is managed by the server, so you can't disable it entirely. However, you can minimize syncing by:\n  - Archiving or deleting unnecessary folders.\n  - Using rules to move emails to specific folders that don\u2019t require frequent access.\n\n---\n\n### **Stop Automatic Folder Synchronization in Outlook Mobile App**\nFor the Outlook mobile app:\n1. Open the Outlook app.\n2. Go to **Settings** (gear icon).\n3. Select the account you want to modify.\n4. Adjust the sync settings under **Sync Email**, **Sync Calendar**, or **Sync Contacts** to control what gets synchronized.\n\n---\n\n### **Considerations**\n- Disabling synchronization may impact your ability to access emails offline or experience delays in receiving new emails.\n- For Exchange or Office 365 accounts, some synchronization is necessary for basic functionality.\n\nIf you need further assistance, let me know your Outlook version and account type, and I can provide more specific guidance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
